se></svg><span class=\"zDocsFeedbackButtonText\"> Feedback</span></span></div></div><div class=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><button aria-label=\"Show topic actions\" data-toggle=\"dropdown\" id=\"zDocsTopicActionsMobile\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-ellipsis-h\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-ellipsis-h\"></use></svg></button><div class=\"dropdown-menu zDocsDropdownMenu zDocsTopicActionsMobileDropdown dropdown-menu-right\"></div></div><div style=\"flex-basis: 100%; height: 0px;\"></div><ul class=\"zDocsTopicPageDetails\"><li class=\"zDocsTopicPageDate css-cinqea\">Last Updated<span class=\"css-cinqea\">Juli 10, 2024</span></li><li class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryDetailsItem\"><button class=\"zDocsAiTopicSummaryButton\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-topic-summary\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-topic-summary\"></use></svg>Summarize</button></li><li class=\"spacer\" role=\"presentation\"></li><div class=\"zDocsLabelWrapper\"><ul><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: Uniface\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=prod_uniface\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>Uniface</a></li><li class=\"zDocsLabel\"><a aria-describedby=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" class=\"css-ettsdk\" data-tooltip-content=\"Search all site by tag: 10.4\" data-tooltip-id=\"hyperLinkFacetsTooltip\" href=\"/de-DE/search?labelkey=uniface_10.4\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-label=\"Tag\" class=\"ico-tag\" role=\"img\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-tag\"></use></svg>10.4</a></li></ul></div></ul></header><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBody\" data-prismjs-copy=\"Copy\" data-prismjs-copy-error=\"Copy failed! Use Ctrl + C instead.\" data-prismjs-copy-success=\"Copied!\"><div class=\"zDocsTopicPageBodyContent\" dir=\"ltr\"><div id=\"zDocsAiSummaryContaineruniface_104gan1665702559756.html\"></div><div><article class=\"hascomments\" data-page=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gan1665702559756.html\" id=\"bundle:uniface_104/enus/gan1665702559756.html\"><main role=\"main\"><article aria-labelledby=\"ariaid-title1\" class=\"dita\" id=\"gan1665702559756\" role=\"article\">\n<h1 class=\"title topictitle1\" id=\"ariaid-title1\">\n      $idpart\n </h1>\n<div class=\"body conbody\" id=\"gan1665702559756___idpart_268106\"><p class=\"shortdesc\">Return the ID part of an associative list item.\n </p>\n<section class=\"section refsyn\" id=\"gan1665702559756__topic_d84293e1_d84294e1_d84295e1\">\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gan1665702559756__p_d84296e1_d84297e1_d84298e1\">\n<span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$idpart</span>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">(</code>\n<var class=\"keyword varname\">AssociativeListItem</var>\n<code class=\"ph codeph\">)</code>\n</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gan1665702559756__topic_d55832e1_d55833e1_d55834e1_d55835e1_d55836e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d383030e75\">\n                       \n Return Values\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gan1665702559756__p_d84302e1_d84303e1_d84304e1\">ID part of an associative list item.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gan1665702559756__topic_d55837e1_d55838e1_d55839e1_d55840e1_d55841e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d383030e84\">Use</h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gan1665702559756__d5916e20\">Allowed in all component types.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gan1665702559756__topic_d55842e1_d55843e1_d55844e1_d55845e1_d55846e1\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d383030e93\">\n                       \n Description\n </h2>\n<p class=\"p\" id=\"gan1665702559756__p_d84314e1_d84315e1_d84316e1\">For more information, see <a class=\"xref\" data-bundleid=\"uniface_104\" data-navpath=\"ayl1665702554178.html\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ayl1665702554178.html\" title=\"A list is a group of related items homogeneous items collected into a single unit, the list. Every item in a list is assumed to have the same structure.\">Lists and Sublists</a>.</p>\n</section>\n<section class=\"section\" id=\"gan1665702559756__section_r3g_f21_1cc\"><h2 class=\"title sectiontitle\" id=\"d383030e110\">Example: Extracting the ID and Value of an Associative List Item</h2>\n<div class=\"div\">\n<p class=\"p\">\n               The following example shows how the <span class=\"keyword cmdname\">$valuepart</span> function can be\n               used to extract the value part of an associative list item:</p>\n<div class=\"code-toolbar\"><pre class=\"pre language-plaintext\" id=\"gan1665702559756__pre_w11_g21_1cc\" tabindex=\"0\"><code class=\"language-plaintext\">$1 = $idpart(\"Key=TheData\")\n$2 = $valuepart(\"Key=TheData\")\n; results:\n; $1 = \"Key\"\n; $2 = \"TheData\"\n</code></pre><div class=\"toolbar\"><div class=\"toolbar-item\"><button class=\"copy-to-clipboard-button\" data-copy-state=\"copy\" type=\"button\"><span>Copy</span></button></div></div></div>\n</div>\n</section>\n</div>\n</article></main></article>\n</div></div><div class=\"contentPlaceholder\" style=\"height: 500px;\"><div class=\"contentContainer zDocsSideBoxes\"><div><h5 aria-level=\"5\" class=\"css-g931ng\">Related Links</h5><ul><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cip1665702554022.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>List Handling in ProcScript</a><p>Uniface provides ProcScript instructions that enable you to build lists, retrieve items from lists, and sort lists based on various criteria.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/cka1665702557531.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>Associative Lists</a><p>Each item in an associative list consists of a pair of associated values separated by an equal sign (=), such as a property and its value, or a value and its representation.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ovl1720066762191.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>getitem</a><p>Copy an item from a list to a field or variable.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/quu1665702559831.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$item</a><p>Return the value that corresponds to a given ID in an associative list.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/ytj1665702559912.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$valuepart</a><p>Return the value part of an associative list item.</p></li><li><a class=\"css-ettsdk\" href=\"/de-DE/bundle/uniface_104/page/bzk1665702559988.html\" stylesprops=\"[object Object]\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-related-link\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-related-link\"></use></svg>$itemnr</a><p>Return the list item that corresponds to a given index number in a list.</p></li></ul></div></div></div></div><div class=\"bottomFeedback\"><div aria-labelledby=\"bottomFeedbackText\" class=\"bottomFeedbackContent\" role=\"group\"><span class=\"bottomFeedbackText\" id=\"bottomFeedbackText\">Was this topic helpful?</span><div class=\"bottomFeedbackButtonGroup\"><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527771\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-up\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-up\"></use></svg><span>Like</span></a><a data-backdrop=\"static\" data-target=\"#feedbackModal_bottom_2527771\" data-toggle=\"modal\" href=\"#\" role=\"button\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-thumbs-down\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-thumbs-down\"></use></svg><span>Dislike</span></a></div></div></div><div style=\"position: fixed; bottom: 170px; right: 70px; cursor: pointer; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: linear; transition-delay: 0s; z-index: 3; opacity: 0; visibility: hidden; transition-property: opacity, visibility;\"><button aria-label=\"Scroll to top\" class=\"zDocsScrollTopBtn\" data-tooltip-content=\"Scroll to top\" data-tooltip-id=\"zDocsBackToTopToolTip\" id=\"zDocsScrollToTop\" type=\"button\"><svg aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"ico-next\"><use xlink:href=\"#ico-next\"></use></svg></button></div></body></html>", "text": "$idpart Add to My Topics Add selected topic and subtopics Add Topic & Subtopics with topic head Add entire publication Watch Download PDF Save selected topic Save selected topic and subtopics Save entire publication Share Email Link Copy Link Feedback Last Updated Juli 10, 2024 Summarize Uniface 10.4 $idpart Return the ID part of an associative list item. $idpart ( AssociativeListItem ) Return Values ID part of an associative list item. Use Allowed in all component types. Description For more information, see Lists and Sublists . Example: Extracting the ID and Value of an Associative List Item The following example shows how the $valuepart function can be used to extract the value part of an associative list item: $1 = $idpart(\"Key=TheData\") $2 = $valuepart(\"Key=TheData\") ; results: ; $1 = \"Key\" ; $2 = \"TheData\" Copy Related Links List Handling in ProcScript Uniface provides ProcScript instructions that enable you to build lists, retrieve items from lists, and sort lists based on various criteria. Associative Lists Each item in an associative list consists of a pair of associated values separated by an equal sign (=), such as a property and its value, or a value and its representation. getitem Copy an item from a list to a field or variable. $item Return the value that corresponds to a given ID in an associative list. $valuepart Return the value part of an associative list item. $itemnr Return the list item that corresponds to a given index number in a list. Was this topic helpful? Like Dislike"}